## Phase 1: Split pyproject.toml Dependencies

The current `pyproject.toml` bundles all deps — API, CLI, and worker — into `[project.dependencies]`. This creates a ~3 GB Docker image dominated by `torch` and `open-clip-torch`, none of which are needed by the API server.

Move the following from `[project.dependencies]` to `[project.optional-dependencies] worker`:

```toml
[project.optional-dependencies]
worker = [
    "pillow>=10.0",
    "rawpy>=0.26.1",
    "pyvips>=3.1.1",
    "imagehash>=4.3.0",
    "opencv-python-headless>=4.8.0",
    "requests>=2.25",
    "moondream>=0.0.5",
    "pyexiftool>=0.5",
    "mediapipe>=0.10.0,<0.11",
    "rapidfuzz>=3.0.0",
    "reverse_geocoder>=1.5",
    "torch>=2.10.0",
    "open-clip-torch>=3.3.0",
]
```

After this change:
- `uv sync --frozen --no-dev` → installs API + CLI deps only (lean, ~300 MB image). uv does not install optional extras by default, so worker packages are excluded without any extra flags. This is the correct behavior for the API Docker image.
- `uv sync --frozen --no-dev --extra worker` → installs everything (fat worker image, ~3 GB)
- **Local dev workflow change required**: `uv sync` alone will no longer install worker extras. Update your local sync command (and any README/contributing notes) to `uv sync --all-extras` to restore the full dev environment with all worker packages.

**Verification**: Confirm `src/api/main.py` and all imported modules under `src/api/` do not import any module in the `worker` extra list. The API only imports `fastapi`, `sqlmodel`, `alembic`, `pydantic`, `psycopg2`, `pgvector`, `python-ulid`, `PyYAML`, `uvicorn`, and standard library modules.

