## Phase 2: Dockerfile

File: `Dockerfile` (project root)

```dockerfile
# Build stage — install Python deps using uv
FROM python:3.12-slim AS builder

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    build-essential \
    libpq-dev \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

COPY --from=ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:latest /uv /usr/local/bin/uv

WORKDIR /app
COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./
RUN uv sync --frozen --no-dev

# Runtime stage — minimal image with only what's needed to run
FROM python:3.12-slim

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    libpq5 \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:latest /uv /usr/local/bin/uv
COPY --from=builder /app/.venv /app/.venv
COPY src/ src/
COPY migrations/ migrations/
COPY alembic-control.ini alembic-tenant.ini ./
COPY scripts/ scripts/

ENV PATH="/app/.venv/bin:$PATH"
ENV PYTHONPATH="/app"

EXPOSE 8000

CMD ["uvicorn", "src.api.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000", "--workers", "2"]
```

**Notes:**
- `--workers 2` is appropriate for the CX32. Increase to 4 if CPU becomes a bottleneck.
- No `--reload` flag in production.
- `uv` is copied into the runtime stage because `scripts/migrate.sh` uses `uv run alembic` and `uv run python` throughout. The venv is already on `PATH` so all Python imports resolve correctly; uv itself is needed as the process runner.
- The `scripts/` directory is included so the `migrate` service profile can run `scripts/migrate.sh` from within the same image.
- `.dockerignore` (create at project root) should exclude `.venv/`, `tests/`, `docs/`, `.git/`, `src/ui/`, `*.pyc`, `__pycache__/`.

