## Phase 3: docker-compose.prod.yml

File: `docker-compose.prod.yml` (project root, committed to git)

This file is used **on the server** only. It is not used locally. The existing `docker-compose.yml` (dev infrastructure) remains unchanged.

```yaml
# Production stack. Runs on the VPS.
# Usage:
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml run --rm migrate
#   docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml pull api && docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d api

services:
  caddy:
    image: caddy:2-alpine
    container_name: lumiverb-caddy
    ports:
      - "80:80"
      - "443:443"
      - "443:443/udp"   # HTTP/3
    volumes:
      - ./caddy/Caddyfile:/etc/caddy/Caddyfile:ro
      - caddy_data:/data
      - caddy_config:/config
      - /opt/lumiverb/web:/srv/web:ro
    depends_on:
      - api
    restart: unless-stopped

  api:
    image: ghcr.io/GITHUB_ORG/lumiverb-api:latest
    container_name: lumiverb-api
    environment:
      CONTROL_PLANE_DATABASE_URL: "postgresql+psycopg2://app:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@postgres:5432/control_plane"
      QUICKWIT_URL: "http://quickwit:7280"
      DATA_DIR: "/data/storage"
      ADMIN_KEY: "${ADMIN_KEY}"
    volumes:
      - storage_data:/data/storage
    depends_on:
      postgres:
        condition: service_healthy
      quickwit:
        condition: service_healthy
    restart: unless-stopped
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "curl -sf http://localhost:8000/health || exit 1"]
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3

  migrate:
    image: ghcr.io/GITHUB_ORG/lumiverb-api:latest
    container_name: lumiverb-migrate
    command: ["bash", "scripts/migrate.sh"]
    environment:
      CONTROL_PLANE_DATABASE_URL: "postgresql+psycopg2://app:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@postgres:5432/control_plane"
    depends_on:
      postgres:
        condition: service_healthy
    profiles:
      - migrate

  postgres:
    image: pgvector/pgvector:pg16
    container_name: lumiverb-postgres
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: app
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: "${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}"
      POSTGRES_DB: control_plane
      POSTGRES_HOST_AUTH_METHOD: md5
    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
      - ./scripts/docker/postgres-init.sql:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/01-init.sql:ro
      - ./scripts/docker/02-pg-hba.sh:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d/02-pg-hba.sh:ro
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U app -d control_plane"]
      interval: 5s
      retries: 10
    restart: unless-stopped

  quickwit:
    image: quickwit/quickwit:0.8.1
    container_name: lumiverb-quickwit
    volumes:
      - quickwit_data:/quickwit/qwdata
    environment:
      QW_ENABLE_OTLP_ENDPOINT: "false"
    command: run
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "curl -sf http://localhost:7280/health/livez || exit 1"]
      interval: 10s
      timeout: 5s
      retries: 10
    restart: unless-stopped

volumes:
  postgres_data:
  quickwit_data:
  caddy_data:
  caddy_config:
  storage_data:
```

**`GITHUB_ORG` placeholder**: Replace with the actual GitHub organization/user name that owns the repository. The image name `ghcr.io/GITHUB_ORG/lumiverb-api` must match exactly what is pushed by CI.

**`storage_data` volume**: This named Docker volume holds all proxy and thumbnail files. It survives `docker compose down` and `docker compose down` (without `-v`). Treat it as durable data. Do NOT run `docker compose down -v` in production.

**Why `migrate` uses a profile**: Running migrations is an explicit deploy step, not something that happens automatically on container start. The `profiles: [migrate]` pattern means the migrate service is invisible to `docker compose up -d` and must be invoked deliberately with `docker compose run --rm migrate`. This prevents accidental migration runs and makes the migration step visible in CI logs.

