## Phase 6: Server Provisioning Runbook

This is a one-time setup. Execute in order.

### 1. Provision the server

Create a Hetzner CX32 instance:
- Location: Ashburn, VA (US East) or Nuremberg (EU)
- OS: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS
- Add your personal SSH key during provisioning

### 2. Install Docker

```bash
# As root on the server
apt-get update
apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl
install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] \
  https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(. /etc/os-release && echo "$VERSION_CODENAME") stable" \
  > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list
apt-get update
apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
```

### 3. Create the deploy user and directory

```bash
# As root
useradd -m -s /bin/bash deploy
usermod -aG docker deploy

mkdir -p /opt/lumiverb/web
mkdir -p /opt/lumiverb/caddy
chown -R deploy:deploy /opt/lumiverb
```

### 4. Add deploy SSH key

Generate a deploy keypair (do this locally, not on the server):

```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "lumiverb-deploy" -f ~/.ssh/lumiverb_deploy -N ""
```

Add the public key to the server:

```bash
# On the server as root
mkdir -p /home/deploy/.ssh
echo "PUBLIC_KEY_CONTENT_HERE" >> /home/deploy/.ssh/authorized_keys
chmod 700 /home/deploy/.ssh
chmod 600 /home/deploy/.ssh/authorized_keys
chown -R deploy:deploy /home/deploy/.ssh
```

Add the **private key** (`~/.ssh/lumiverb_deploy`) as the `DEPLOY_SSH_KEY` GitHub Actions secret.

### 5. Configure DNS

Point the domain (e.g. `lumiverb.example.com`) A record at the server IP. Wait for propagation before starting Caddy — Caddy will fail TLS provisioning if the domain doesn't resolve correctly.

### 6. Place production files on the server

From the repo root on your local machine:

```bash
# Copy the production compose file and Caddy config
scp -i ~/.ssh/lumiverb_deploy docker-compose.prod.yml deploy@SERVER_IP:/opt/lumiverb/docker-compose.prod.yml
scp -i ~/.ssh/lumiverb_deploy caddy/Caddyfile deploy@SERVER_IP:/opt/lumiverb/caddy/Caddyfile
scp -i ~/.ssh/lumiverb_deploy -r scripts/ deploy@SERVER_IP:/opt/lumiverb/scripts/
```

### 7. Create the .env file on the server

SSH to the server as `deploy` and create `/opt/lumiverb/.env`:

```bash
cat > /opt/lumiverb/.env << 'EOF'
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<generate with: openssl rand -hex 32>
ADMIN_KEY=<generate with: openssl rand -hex 32>
EOF
chmod 600 /opt/lumiverb/.env
```

This file is never committed to git. It lives only on the server. Back it up securely (1Password, etc.).

### 8. Authenticate Docker with GHCR on the server

```bash
# As deploy user on the server
echo "GITHUB_TOKEN_VALUE" | docker login ghcr.io -u GITHUB_USERNAME --stdin
```

Use a GitHub Personal Access Token with `read:packages` scope. This allows the server to pull private images from GHCR.

### 9. Start the stack

```bash
# As deploy user
cd /opt/lumiverb
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d
```

Caddy will provision a TLS certificate on first start. Check logs if it fails:
```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml logs caddy
```

### 10. Initialize the first tenant

```bash
# On the server — load env, run init script
source /opt/lumiverb/.env
export API_URL=https://lumiverb.example.com
export ADMIN_KEY=$ADMIN_KEY

# Wait for API to be healthy, then create default tenant
curl -sf "$API_URL/health"
curl -s -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name": "default", "plan": "free"}' \
  "$API_URL/v1/admin/tenants"
```

The response contains the tenant API key. Configure the local CLI:
```bash
lumiverb config set --api-url https://lumiverb.example.com --api-key <key from response>
```

