## What Is NOT in Scope

- Worker deployment to the server (workers run locally, on the machine where source files live)
- Horizontal scaling (single-instance API is sufficient until well beyond initial launch)
- Multi-tenant Quickwit isolation (single Quickwit instance serves all tenants; index names are prefixed by tenant_id)
- Rate limiting (deferred to Phase 5 per architecture.md)
- TLS client certificates or mTLS
- Log aggregation beyond `docker compose logs` (add Loki/Grafana when debugging blind becomes a problem)
